In some cases, phenylethanoids, which are phenethyl alcohol-structured phenolic antioxidants, were abundantly found in olive leaves, including oleuropein and its derivatives, followed by tyrosol and verbascoside. These molecules may conduct to its high antioxidant properties
11, 49 . Tyrosol existed in highest concentration in rosemary (4.56 mg g −1), but in small quantity in olive leaf (0.75 mg g −1) and rue (0.19 mg g −1).
